CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1951, pg. 6, reads: "Forty-Six Years - Mr. and Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr. observed their trek down memory lane Sept. 6 with a quiet day at home. This well-known business couple has two sons, Thomas L. West Jr., and Raymond.  They are of old Virginia stock, which just 'fades away.'  Mr. West has been a deacon in Ebenezer Baptist Church for thirty-eight years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas L. West holding pipe, and Nellie Cumphries West, seated on steps in between columns inscribed "Fritz Roneck, Pittsburgh," at their home, 608 Duff Street, Hill District
